name: Gateway of India
description: Iconic basalt arch offering harbor views and ferry links to Elephanta Caves.

name: Marine Drive
description: 3.6 km boulevard facing the Arabian Sea, perfect for sunset walks and night drives.

name: Colaba Causeway Market
description: Bustling street market mixing colonial-era cafes with indie boutiques.

name: Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Vastu Sangrahalaya
description: Premier museum with Indo-Saracenic architecture and curated South Asian art.

name: Chor Bazaar
description: Historic flea market famed for antiques, film posters, and quirky collectibles.

name: Crawford Market
description: Victorian-era fresh produce and gourmet bazaar under stained glass skylights.

name: Sanjay Gandhi National Park
description: 772 sq km protected forest with Kanheri Caves, lion safari and cycling tracks.

name: Kanheri Caves
description: Ancient Buddhist basalt caves carved between 1st and 10th century CE.

name: Powai Lake
description: Picturesque artificial lake flanked by IIT Bombay and lively promenades.

name: Bandra Fort
description: Sea-facing Portuguese fort ruins overlooking the Bandra-Worli Sea Link.

name: Mount Mary Basilica
description: 170-year-old basilica famed for the annual Bandra Fair and votive candles.

name: Juhu Beach
description: Broad sandy stretch loved for sunsets, street snacks, and morning joggers.

name: Versova Village
description: Charming fishing village blending Koli heritage with boho cafes.

name: Elephanta Caves
description: UNESCO-listed basalt cave temples with monumental Shiva sculptures.

name: Global Vipassana Pagoda
description: Golden meditation pagoda with 600ft diameter dome across Gorai creek.

name: Taraporevala Aquarium
description: India's oldest aquarium with 2,000+ fish and touch pools.

name: Nehru Planetarium
description: Dome theatre projecting immersive astronomy shows.

name: Worli Sea Face
description: Wave-battered promenade with skyline views and monsoon spray.

name: Haji Ali Dargah
description: Floating 15th-century dargah connected by a dramatic causeway.

name: Siddhivinayak Temple
description: Grand Ganesha temple drawing daily queues of devotees.

name: Veermata Jijabai Bhosale Zoo
description: Historic city zoo featuring aviaries, reptile houses, and botanical gardens.
